You can try `limit = 10` for a while... to understand why I wanted to add colors. It can be a tad hard to parse things without them. This is to make multiple markets readability on the off chance somebody could be using them and that they don't have to configure `format` out of the box... assuming default `format` is not awful.

```
# color just works without adding anything
coin_markets {
    limit = 10
}
```
```
# color just works without adding anything
coin_markets {
    markets = ['btc', 'dash', 'eth', 'sky'] 
}
```

